    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-13T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="738"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5034 China—Searchlight Publishing Co./35:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JPR1"
                            type="from">Josselyn</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-13T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 13, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 13—10:19 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>389. Department’s 247, September 8, 6 p.m. <hi rend="italic">China Forum</hi> has
                    not been published subsequent to issue of August 13th. I am informed this is
                    because <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> has been unable
                    at this time get any firm or person to print it; Chinese and nonextraterritorial
                    printers are unwilling to print it because of probable prosecution in Chinese
                    courts. International Settlement police have information that <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> is now trying to buy his own
                    printing press but he has not yet done so.</p>
                <p>If and when <hi rend="italic">China Forum</hi> is again published this Consulate
                    General will, unless the character of its articles has changed, follow
                    Department’s instructions but in the meantime it seems preferable to take no
                    action.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JPR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
